UNITED STATES ex rel. Armin VOLK, Relator-Appellant, v. Benjamin M. DAY, Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of New York, etc., Respondent-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 20, 1928. No. 226. William W. Brown, of New York City (James C. Thomas, of New York City, and Roger O’Donnell, of Washington, D. C., of counsel), for appellant. ' Charles H. Tuttle, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Abbot Low Moffat, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed.
